If you want to prevent the user deleting text, that should be done with a [`TextFormatter`](https://openjfx.io/javadoc/16/javafx.controls/javafx/scene/control/TextFormatter.html) instead of trying to guess which key events the control is handling internally, and in what order all those events are handled, etc. etc., for its default behavior.

It&#39;s not clear exactly what you want to achieve, but here is an example, which prevents any deletion (or replacement) of text:

    public class Terminal {
        @FXML
        private TextArea taConsole;
    
        @FXML
        protected void initialize(){
            taConsole.setText(&quot;&gt;&quot;);
            taConsole.positionCaret(1);
            taConsole.setTextFormatter(new TextFormatter(change -&gt; {
                if (change.getRangeStart() == change.getRangeEnd()) { // nothing deleted
                    return change ;
                }
                // change represents a deletion of some text, veto it:
                return null ;
            });
        }
    
    }

See the [Javadocs for `TextFormatter.Change`](https://openjfx.io/javadoc/16/javafx.controls/javafx/scene/control/TextFormatter.Change.html) for details.

