The first step is to top ignoring potential errors and implement `onCancelled`. 

At its minimum this should look like:
```
public void onCancelled(@NonNull DatabaseError databaseError) { 
    throw databaseError.toException(); 
}
```

Or:

```
public void onCancelled(@NonNull DatabaseError databaseError) { 
    Log.e(&quot;Firebase&quot;, databaseError.toException());
}
```

If this shows an exception coming from the database, I recommend searching for that error message, as it&#39;s likely been covered before.

